<blockquote><div class=background></div><div class=copy>
<h1>
Circos Collaborates with Wired
</h1>
<p>
<p>When <a href="http://www.wired.com">Wired</a> needed an inforgraphic to illustrate the complex world of relationships on the TV Series Lost, it turned to Circos.

<p>The task was to visually represent about 60 relationships shared between 35 characters. The <a href="
/circos/presentations/articles/vis_tables1">tableviewer</a> utility, which applies Circos to visualizing tabular data, was perfect for creating the <a href="http://www.wired.com/magazine/2010/04/ff_lost/5/">illustration</a>. And thus, Circos <a href="/circos/tableviewer">says goodbye to the table</a>.</p>
</p>
<div class=annot>// wired-04</div>
</div></blockquote>
</div> <!-- page-masthead -->
